Description: Vital Restoration is a restoration company focusing on residential and commercial interior damages.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: San Francisco Bay Area based Vital Restoration provides best and reliable disaster restoration services to both commercial and residential fronts. It has IICRC certified trained experts who are equipped with equipments that helps them restore the things into their previous state. Whether you have a business or a home or a rental that has faced a problem of disaster due to water, fire damage or any other sort of damage, you can always believe in them. Vital Restoration provides a work done with excellence and places the highest quality of workmanship in all its assignments whether it is large or small. The team here not only restores the space and its contents after a disaster, but also takes care to prevent future problems. Depending on the damage, restoration could be as a basic cleaning or as extensive as a major recovery project, using special equipment designed to clear away smoke or water damage. Whatever the cause of the damage, Vital Restoration is able to assess and repair the situation, day or night. Vital Restoration has a series of damage restoration services that includes: Fire Damage: The damage caused by a fire is quite expensive to repair; the experts at Vital Restoration use the latest technologies and the most specialized skills to remove smoke, soot and accompanying odors throughout the structure. Not only do our experts repair structural damage, they also photograph, document, clean and pack down any contents that may have been affected.  Smoke Damage: Although smoke damage often accompanies fire damage, the effects of the smoke can often exceed the effects of the flames. In such instances, the Vital Restoration team will perform expert cleaning and odor removal techniques, including the use of air scrubbers with activated charcoal filters, in order to ensure complete and thorough odor elimination. Water Damage: To help homeowners and property owners minimize the damage caused by water penetration, Vital Restoration responds quickly and aggressively. By providing fast response to the scene, Vital Restoration helps to mitigate the damage caused by water.  Carpet Cleaning: Too often, the carpet is overlooked in the restoration process, or is sometimes deemed irreparable. Before getting rid of the carpet completely, the IICRC certified carpet and upholstery cleaners at Vital Restoration use modern technology to clean deep beneath the surface, where debris and moisture can linger and cause odor.  Sewage Cleanup: Sewage cleanup is not only an annoying pain; it is also a health hazard. The microorganisms that live in sewage can be harmful and so any sewage cleanup must be done as soon as possible. House Restoration: Whether your home or property suffers from smoke, fire, water or other type of damage, the team at Vital Restoration is reachable at any time to help assist with your needs.

Description: CameraFTP offers a revolutionary cloud-based security monitoring and storage service.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: CameraFTP offers a revolutionary cloud-based security and monitoring service. Unlike services offered by ADT and other security companies, CameraFTP service is extremely easy to setup, the cost is extremely low, and with its cloud-based technology, you can remotely monitor the scene or play back the recorded footage from anywhere on any device. Because the data is stored in CameraFTP's secure data center, it is far more secure than traditional security services. Today, network security cameras are no longer expensive or complicated. By utilizing low-cost network cameras and CameraFTP service, consumers and businesses can enjoy better service than traditional CCTV security systems at a much lower cost. CameraFTP also offers software based security camera for free. With our software, you can turn a webcam, a smartphone or a tablet into a network security camera at no cost! Under the hood, CameraFTP offers a special FTP service that is fully optimized for network security cameras. It supports almost all network cameras and software-based security cameras. CameraFTP is operated by Drive Headquarters, Inc. (DriveHQ). Based in Silicon Valley, DriveHQ is the first Cloud IT Solution provider, offering a wide range of cloud IT services. DriveHQ is also one of the largest FTP hosting service providers. A conventional FTP server that runs on a Linux or Windows server cannot support tens of thousands of users; however, CameraFTP's FTP server can easily handle tens of millions of users.  CameraFTP is different from any regular FTP services. A network camera may automatically upload images or videos to the FTP server every second. Compared with a regular person, who probably only uploads a few files per day, a network camera can create 100 times or even 1000 times more load than a regular person. To support millions of network cameras, an FTP system must be extremely efficient and scalable. Built on DriveHQ’s highly scalable FTP platform, CameraFTP offers more optimized service to network camera users. The service is more reliable, more efficient, more functional and more secure than any regular FTP services.

Description: Therapeutics for Cancer and Viruses
Full Description: Savoy Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (“Savoy”) develops innovative products to treat, heal, and improve the quality of life for patients in the fields of oncology and virology.   The company’s first product is a unique treatment targeted to a protein found on the surface of Hepatitis C (HCV) infected liver cells, HIV infected cells, and Hepatocellular carcinoma (liver cancer).  Savoy’s technology is based on the company’s revolutionary discovery that TK1 is expressed on HCV infected cells, HIV infected cells and liver cancers, and is not found on the surface of any normal cell type.  The company has developed a fully human monoclonal antibody that binds specifically to TK1 on the surface of liver cancer directly attributable to the Hepatitis C Virus, HCV infected cells, HCV and HIV co-infected cells (HCV/HIV). The company has performed the preclinical testing required to demonstrate that our antibody binds to and kills cancerous cells while causing no harm to any normal cells or tissues in the body. This is a major breakthrough in the war against cancer and opens the door to unique therapeutic applications using the antibody.

Description: A non-profit performing arts organization.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Founded in 1967 by dedicated local parents and a high school teacher, the Santa Clara Vanguard has grown into the premier non-profit performing arts organization in Santa Clara County. Each year, approximately 350 young men and women experience an immersive program that provides intense performance instruction in music, dance, movement, and performance in the areas of brass, percussion and color guard. Members perform almost every other night each summer for six to eight weeks while traveling 25,000 miles across the United States in competition. With five thousand alumni and growing each year, Vanguard is a highly regarded institution within the local and national marching music communities. In the Fall of 2013 Vanguard launched the Community Performing Arts program, which includes; a private music lesson program for elementary, middle and high school students, at below market cost. Our Santa Clara Big Band brings community members together for performances at various local events including Music in the Park during the Holiday season. After a strong start, we are looking forward to our Community based programs bringing more music and music education to Silicon Valley.
